## Background

Users need intuitive controls to show/hide overlays and adjust their transparency. These controls should be in the Layers section of the sidebar.

## Task

Implement overlay visibility controls:

1. **Control layout**:
```tsx
<div className="space-y-4">
    {/* Master toggle */}
    <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <span className="font-medium">Overlay</span>
        <Toggle
            checked={overlayVisible}
            onChange={setOverlayVisible}
        />
    </div>

    {/* Opacity slider (when visible) */}
    {overlayVisible && (
        <div className="space-y-2">
            <div className="flex justify-between text-sm">
                <span>Opacity</span>
                <span>{Math.round(opacity * 100)}%</span>
            </div>
            <input
                type="range"
                min={0}
                max={100}
                value={opacity * 100}
                onChange={e => setOpacity(e.target.value / 100)}
                className="w-full"
            />
        </div>
    )}

    {/* Per-class toggles (optional) */}
    {overlayVisible && classes.length > 0 && (
        <div className="space-y-1">
            <button 
                onClick={() => setClassesExpanded(!classesExpanded)}
                className="text-sm text-gray-500"
            >
                {classesExpanded ? 'Hide' : 'Show'} classes
            </button>
            {classesExpanded && (
                <div className="pl-4 space-y-1">
                    {classes.map(cls => (
                        <label key={cls.id} className="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <input
                                type="checkbox"
                                checked={visibleClasses.includes(cls.id)}
                                onChange={() => toggleClass(cls.id)}
                            />
                            <span 
                                className="w-3 h-3 rounded" 
                                style={{ backgroundColor: cls.color }}
                            />
                            <span className="text-sm">{cls.name}</span>
                        </label>
                    ))}
                </div>
            )}
        </div>
    )}
</div>
```

2. **State management**:
```typescript
const [overlayVisible, setOverlayVisible] = useState(true);
const [opacity, setOpacity] = useState(0.7);
const [visibleClasses, setVisibleClasses] = useState<number[]>([]);

const toggleClass = (classId: number) => {
    setVisibleClasses(prev =>
        prev.includes(classId)
            ? prev.filter(id => id !== classId)
            : [...prev, classId]
    );
};
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Master toggle shows/hides overlay
- [ ] Opacity slider adjusts transparency
- [ ] Toggle response < 100ms
- [ ] Opacity adjustment smooth (no lag)
- [ ] Per-class toggles work (optional)
- [ ] State persists during session

## Why This Matters

Clear controls:
- Let users customize their view
- Reduce visual clutter when needed
- Enable focus on specific areas
- Standard expectation for overlay tools

