## Background

Micro-animations make interfaces feel responsive and polished. They provide feedback, guide attention, and add delight without slowing users down.

## Task

Implement animation system:

1. **Animation timing tokens**:
```css
--duration-instant: 0ms;
--duration-fast: 150ms;
--duration-normal: 250ms;
--duration-slow: 400ms;
--easing-default: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
--easing-in: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1);
--easing-out: cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1);
```

2. **Specific animations**:

| Element | Animation | Duration | Easing |
|---------|-----------|----------|--------|
| Sidebar expand/collapse | Width + opacity | 250ms | ease-out |
| Section expand | Height + opacity | 200ms | ease-out |
| Button hover | Background color | 150ms | ease |
| Toggle switch | Transform + color | 150ms | ease |
| Loading skeleton | Pulse (opacity) | 1.5s | ease-in-out |
| Notification enter | Slide + fade | 200ms | ease-out |
| Notification exit | Fade | 150ms | ease-in |
| Viewport snap | Pan/zoom | 300-500ms | ease-out |

3. **Animation utilities**:
```tsx
// Framer Motion or CSS-based
const sidebarVariants = {
    open: { width: 280, opacity: 1 },
    closed: { width: 0, opacity: 0 }
};

// Or Tailwind
<div className="transition-all duration-250 ease-out" />
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Sidebar animates smoothly
- [ ] Section expand/collapse animated
- [ ] Button states transition smoothly
- [ ] Toggle switches have clear animations
- [ ] Loading states have subtle animation
- [ ] No janky or stuttering animations
- [ ] Animations respect reduced-motion preference

## Reduced Motion Support

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * {
        animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
        transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    }
}
```

## Why This Matters

Micro-animations:
- Provide instant feedback
- Guide user attention
- Make app feel responsive
- Add polish and delight

