## Background

Power users prefer keyboard shortcuts. Essential actions should have intuitive shortcuts that don't conflict with browser defaults.

## Task

Implement keyboard shortcuts:

1. **Shortcut assignments**:

| Shortcut | Action | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| `Ctrl/Cmd + \\` | Toggle sidebar | Common for panels |
| `Ctrl/Cmd + 0` | Reset zoom to fit | Standard zoom reset |
| `Ctrl/Cmd + F` | Toggle follow presenter | F for Follow |
| `Ctrl/Cmd + L` | Copy share link | L for Link |
| `Escape` | Exit follow mode / close panels | Standard escape |
| `?` | Show keyboard shortcuts help | Common convention |

2. **Implementation**:
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
    const handleKeydown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
        const ctrl = e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey;

        switch (true) {
            case ctrl && e.key === '\\':
                e.preventDefault();
                toggleSidebar();
                break;
            case ctrl && e.key === '0':
                e.preventDefault();
                resetZoom();
                break;
            case ctrl && e.key === 'f' && \!isPresenter:
                e.preventDefault();
                toggleFollow();
                break;
            case ctrl && e.key === 'l':
                e.preventDefault();
                copyShareLink();
                break;
            case e.key === 'Escape':
                exitFollowMode();
                closePanels();
                break;
            case e.key === '?':
                showShortcutsHelp();
                break;
        }
    };

    window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeydown);
    return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeydown);
}, [/* deps */]);
```

3. **Shortcuts help modal**:
   - Show on `?` key press
   - List all shortcuts in organized table
   - Dismissable with Escape

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All listed shortcuts work
- [ ] No conflicts with browser shortcuts
- [ ] Shortcuts work regardless of focus
- [ ] Help modal shows all shortcuts
- [ ] Shortcuts shown in tooltips
- [ ] Works on Mac and Windows

## Why This Matters

Keyboard shortcuts:
- Speed up power user workflows
- Improve accessibility
- Enable mouse-free operation
- Signal professional-grade software

