Phase 5: Visual Polish (PathCollab-zavx)

## Background

An in-app log view allows users to see and share recent activity without needing browser DevTools. This is especially useful for bug reports.

## Task

Implement log viewer:

1. **Log capture**:
```typescript
const MAX_LOGS = 100;

type LogEntry = {
    timestamp: Date;
    level: 'info' | 'warn' | 'error' | 'debug';
    category: string;
    message: string;
    data?: any;
};

class LogCollector {
    private logs: LogEntry[] = [];
    private listeners: Set<(logs: LogEntry[]) => void> = new Set();

    log(level: LogEntry['level'], category: string, message: string, data?: any) {
        const entry: LogEntry = {
            timestamp: new Date(),
            level,
            category,
            message,
            data
        };

        this.logs.push(entry);
        if (this.logs.length > MAX_LOGS) {
            this.logs.shift();
        }

        this.notify();
    }

    getLogs() { return [...this.logs]; }

    subscribe(listener: (logs: LogEntry[]) => void) {
        this.listeners.add(listener);
        return () => this.listeners.delete(listener);
    }

    private notify() {
        this.listeners.forEach(l => l(this.logs));
    }
}

export const logger = new LogCollector();
```

2. **Log viewer component**:
```tsx
function LogViewer() {
    const [logs, setLogs] = useState<LogEntry[]>([]);
    const [filter, setFilter] = useState<string>('');

    useEffect(() => {
        return logger.subscribe(setLogs);
    }, []);

    const filteredLogs = logs.filter(l => 
        filter === '' || l.category.includes(filter) || l.message.includes(filter)
    );

    const copyLogs = () => {
        const text = filteredLogs.map(l => 
            `[${l.timestamp.toISOString()}] [${l.level}] [${l.category}] ${l.message}`
        ).join('\n');
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
    };

    return (
        <div className="space-y-2">
            <div className="flex gap-2">
                <input 
                    placeholder="Filter..." 
                    value={filter}
                    onChange={e => setFilter(e.target.value)}
                    className="flex-1 text-sm px-2 py-1 border rounded"
                />
                <Button size="sm" onClick={copyLogs}>Copy</Button>
            </div>
            <div className="h-40 overflow-y-auto bg-gray-900 rounded p-2 font-mono text-xs">
                {filteredLogs.map((log, i) => (
                    <div key={i} className={`${levelColors[log.level]}`}>
                        [{log.level[0].toUpperCase()}] [{log.category}] {log.message}
                    </div>
                ))}
            </div>
        </div>
    );
}
```

3. **Integration points**:
   - WebSocket messages: `logger.log('debug', 'ws', 'Sent: CreateSession')`
   - Tile requests: `logger.log('debug', 'tiles', `Loaded ${level}/${x}/${y}`)`
   - Errors: `logger.log('error', 'overlay', 'Upload failed', error)`

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Log viewer shows last 100 entries
- [ ] Filter works on category and message
- [ ] Copy button copies all visible logs
- [ ] Color coding by log level
- [ ] Scrollable log area
- [ ] No performance impact from logging

## Why This Matters

Log viewer:
- Enables bug report inclusion
- Self-service debugging
- No DevTools required
- Supports quick triage

