## Background

Currently, sharing requires creating a session first. In the new model, sharing should be available immediately - clicking it auto-creates a session if needed.

## Task

Implement always-available Copy Link:

1. **Sidebar placement**:
   - In Session section of sidebar
   - Always visible, never disabled
   - Clear visual affordance (button)

2. **Behavior**:
   - If no session exists  auto-create, then copy link
   - If session exists  copy existing link
   - Show confirmation feedback (tooltip/toast)

3. **Link format**:
   - Uses PUBLIC_BASE_URL for proper URL
   - Single token format: `/s/abc123#t=token`
   - URL works immediately for others

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Copy Link button in sidebar (Session section)
- [ ] Button never disabled (auto-creates if needed)
- [ ] Link copied to clipboard on click
- [ ] Success feedback shown (checkmark, toast)
- [ ] Link uses correct base URL
- [ ] Auto-created session works for joiners

## Implementation

```tsx
function CopyLinkButton() {
    const { session, createSession } = useSession();
    const [copied, setCopied] = useState(false);

    const handleCopy = async () => {
        let shareUrl: string;

        if (!session) {
            // Auto-create session
            const newSession = await createSession();
            shareUrl = newSession.shareUrl;
        } else {
            shareUrl = session.shareUrl;
        }

        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(shareUrl);
        setCopied(true);
        setTimeout(() => setCopied(false), 2000);
    };

    return (
        <button 
            onClick={handleCopy}
            className="flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded"
        >
            {copied ? (
                <>
                    <CheckIcon className="w-4 h-4" />
                    Copied!
                </>
            ) : (
                <>
                    <LinkIcon className="w-4 h-4" />
                    Copy Link
                </>
            )}
        </button>
    );
}
```

## UX Details

- **Button idle**: 'Copy Link' with link icon
- **Button copying**: Brief loading state (optional)
- **Button success**: 'Copied!' with checkmark, auto-revert after 2s
- **Button error**: 'Failed' with retry option

## Why This Matters

One-click sharing is critical for collaboration adoption:
- Reduces friction from 3 clicks to 1
- Makes sharing feel instant
- Encourages collaborative usage

