## Background

Canvas2D is a reliable, well-understood rendering API. WebGL offers better performance but adds complexity. For MVP, Canvas2D provides the best reliability/effort tradeoff.

## Task

Implement Canvas2D overlay rendering:

1. **Overlay layer component**:
```tsx
function OverlayLayer({ overlayId, viewport, opacity }: Props) {
    const canvasRef = useRef<HTMLCanvasElement>(null);
    const [tiles, setTiles] = useState<Map<string, ImageBitmap>>(new Map());

    useEffect(() => {
        if (!canvasRef.current) return;
        const ctx = canvasRef.current.getContext('2d');
        if (!ctx) return;

        // Clear canvas
        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvasRef.current.width, canvasRef.current.height);

        // Set global opacity
        ctx.globalAlpha = opacity;

        // Calculate visible tiles
        const visibleTiles = calculateVisibleTiles(viewport);

        // Draw each tile
        for (const { x, y, level } of visibleTiles) {
            const key = `${level}/${x}/${y}`;
            const tile = tiles.get(key);
            if (tile) {
                const destRect = tileToCanvasRect(x, y, level, viewport);
                ctx.drawImage(tile, destRect.x, destRect.y, destRect.w, destRect.h);
            }
        }
    }, [viewport, tiles, opacity]);

    return (
        <canvas
            ref={canvasRef}
            className="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"
            width={window.innerWidth}
            height={window.innerHeight}
        />
    );
}
```

2. **Tile loading**:
```typescript
const loadTile = async (overlayId: string, level: number, x: number, y: number) => {
    const response = await fetch(`/api/overlays/${overlayId}/tiles/${level}/${x}/${y}`);
    const blob = await response.blob();
    return createImageBitmap(blob);
};
```

3. **Viewport synchronization**:
